    "The most commonly used DL models in AD diagnosis by CAD systems are convolutional neural networks (CNN), recurrent neural networks (RNN), generative adversarial networks (GAN), etc.",
    "Although, the performance of the DL models is superior when they are compared with the traditional ML models, they 30 Page 10 of 62",
    "lack explainability and are computationally expensive.",
    "We further discuss the applicability of these models for AD diagnosis in Sect. 4.",
    "Also, there are bunch of tools available for the researchers and developers to implement the CAD systems."
